## When to use
Use this skill when you need to monitor CPU and memory usage statistics on a Linux system using the vmstat command.

## Approach
To effectively monitor CPU and memory statistics, start by running `vmstat` with specific options that provide detailed information. Use `shell_exec(vmstat -s)` to see comprehensive statistics about system resources, or use `shell_exec(vmstat 1 5)` for continuous monitoring over a period of time to observe the dynamic behavior of your system.

## Example
To monitor system resource usage continuously every second for five cycles, execute:
```
shell_exec("vmstat 1 5")
```

## Pitfalls
- Ensure vmstat is installed on your Linux machine as it may not be present by default.
- Be aware that `vmstat` provides an overview rather than detailed insights into specific processes.